<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="501" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,356,1496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,411,1364,1389]" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">Additional notes.</emphasis>
Although 
<taxonomicName box="[545,660,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xyphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudum">
<emphasis box="[545,660,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">X. nudum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was derived from within a clade comprising the four included specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[316,480,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xyphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis box="[316,480,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">X. reticulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the phylogenetic analyses, the former is morphologically distinct and is here retained as a valid species. More detailed studies will be needed to determine whether 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1217,1436,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xyphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudum">
<emphasis box="[1111,1217,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">X. nudum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extreme color variant of 
<taxonomicName box="[266,425,1471,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xyphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis box="[266,425,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="501">X. reticulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Notes under the latter species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
